<item subject="An XML catalog" url="mailto:debian-sgml@lists.debian.org" urlname="The Debian-SGML mailing-list" taken-by="<nobody>" rating=2 id=__FILE__>

Debian seriously lacks an <a href="http://xmlsoft.org/catalog.html">XML
catalog</a>. It should provide a mapping from the public DOCTYPE
identifers to the DTDs installed on the system. GNOME 2 seriously
needs it, and is currently using gross hacks to work around the
lack of a catalog.<br>
<a href="mailto:mrj@debian.org">Mark Johson</a> once
<a href="http://lists.debian.org/debian-sgml/2002/debian-sgml-200206/msg00000.html">started</a>
to work on it, but he seems to be
<a href="http://lists.debian.org/debian-sgml/2002/debian-sgml-200210/msg00004.html">missing in action</a>.

</item>
